nomic outlook for the medium and long term; as well as the politics of its social policy, focusing on poverty and income distribution, social policy strategies since 1982, and the political challenges posed by the decentralization of political power. The final chapter discusses the changing U.S.-Mexico relationship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh1 aBriggs, Everett Ellis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález Gómez, Mauricio A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Claudio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaufman Purcell, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaufman Purcell, Susan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRubio, Luis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRubio, Luis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTrejo, Guillermo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z97831107842680 cprintz978155587315840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781685858302423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781685858302/original  a978-3-11-078426-8  Lynne Rienner Press Complete Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles